          <div style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 16px 20px; background: rgba(34,197,94,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.2); border-radius: 12px; display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: flex-start;">
             <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#16a34a" stroke-width="2" style="flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px;"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><path d="M12 16v-4"></path><path d="M12 8h.01"></path></svg>
             <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;"><strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA Requires:</strong> A contrast ratio of at least <strong>4.5:1</strong> for normal text (like most button labels) and <strong>3.0:1</strong> for large text and UI components (like icons and focus rings). All UEMS core buttons pass these standards.</p>
          </div>
        </div>



        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="touch-target-size" class="doc-h3">Touch Target Size</h3>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Mobile and tablet platforms require specific tap areas to prevent accidental clicks.</p>
          <div style="margin-top: 16px; padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 24px;">
             <div style="width: 48px; height: 48px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); border: 1px dashed var(--prism-violet); border-radius: 8px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; color: var(--prism-violet); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600;">48px</div>
             <div>
               <div style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 15px; color: var(--prism-text);">Minimum Target: 48×48px</div>
               <div style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-top: 4px;">Small variant buttons (e.g., 36px) will naturally have invisible transparent padding added in physical mobile environments to meet iOS/Android touch spacing requirements.</div>
             </div>
